        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 7:06PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 706 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paulding, or 7 miles southwest of Defiance, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Defiance, Paulding, Continental, Holgate, Melrose, Florida, Latty,
Cecil, Miller City, Broughton, New Bavaria, Kieferville, Jewell,
Arthur, Charloe, Pleasant Bend, Ayersville, The Bend, North Creek,
and Brunersburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
